#Data cleaning and set up

#Renaming economic freedom dataset for convienence
EconomicFreedom <- read_xlsx("World Economy Freedom.xlsx")

#subset economic freedom data to only include country name, 
#year, and overall score
EconomicFreedom <- subset(EconomicFreedom,select=c(2,21))

#renaming GDP data for convienence
GDP <- read_xls("imf-dm-export-20240328.xls")

#subsetting GDP data to only include country and 2022 GDP
GDP <- subset(GDP,select=c(1,44))

#removing rows with no data in GDP set
GDP <- na.omit(GDP)
GDP <- subset(GDP,GDP$`2022`!="no data")

#renaming gdp columns for convenience
colnames(GDP)<- c("Country","GDP2022")
#removing erroneous data from econ freedom set
EconomicFreedom<-EconomicFreedom[2:184,]

#subsetting GDP data to only include countries
#that are in econ freedom set
countries <- EconomicFreedom$`Country Name`
GDP <- GDP[GDP$Country %in% countries,]

#subsetting economic freedom data to only include countries that are in GDP set
countries2 <- GDP$Country
EconomicFreedom <- EconomicFreedom[EconomicFreedom$`Country Name` %in% countries2,]

#renaming gdp columns
colnames(GDP)<-c("Country","GDP2022")

#drop first row of econ freedom dataset before merging
EconomicFreedom <- subset(EconomicFreedom,select=c(2))

#merging the two sets together
GDP_EconomicFreedom <- cbind(GDP,EconomicFreedom)

#setting GDP value as numeric
options(scipen = 999)
GDP_EconomicFreedom <- GDP_EconomicFreedom%>% mutate_at(c('GDP2022'), as.numeric)

#histograms for each variable
GDP_EconomicFreedom|>
  ggplot(aes(x=GDP2022))+
  geom_histogram(color="black",fill="lightblue")+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 10))+
  labs(title="Histogram of GDP Per Capita",
       subtitle="by country, 2022",
       x="GDP Per Capita in USD",
       y="Frequency")+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.50))+
  theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust=0.50))

#calculating correlation coefficient 
cor(GDP_EconomicFreedom$`2022 Score`, GDP_EconomicFreedom$GDP2022, 
    method = "pearson")
## [1] 0.4687988
#scatterplot
GDP_EconomicFreedom|>
  ggplot(aes(x=`2022 Score`,y=GDP2022))+
  geom_point(color="blue")+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE,color="red")+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 10))+
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,80000),
                     breaks = seq(0,80000,by=10000),
                     labels = scales::label_number(suffix = "K",
                                                   scale = 1e-3))+
  labs(title="Scatterplot of GDP per Capita v Economic Freedom Index",
       x="Economic Freedom Index",
       y="GDP Per Capita in USD",
       subtitle = "by country, 2022")+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.50))+
  theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust=0.50))
